{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/automate-my-everythings/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"360 Degrees of Awesome","author":"Mattie Ellins"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a51338bb-033f-5580-b677-fb217ea7e540","excerpt":"I spent some of the day, between tasks, to take a look at “if this then\nthat” or otherwise known as ifttt. ifttt allows you to essentially script events to…","html":"<p>I spent some of the day, between tasks, to take a look at “if this then\nthat” or otherwise known as <a href=\"http://ifttt.com/\">ifttt</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ifttt.com/\">ifttt</a> allows you to essentially script events to actions. For\nexample, I wrote a <a href=\"http://ifttt.com/recipes/40275\">recipe that emails me</a> when<a href=\"http://www.gizmodo.com.au/tags/app-deals-of-the-day/\">Gizmodo’s App Deals</a>\ngets posted, then tells me what mobile applications are on sale for the\nday via email.</p>\n<p>I got a bit excited and went through some of the recipes that were on\ndisplay and ended up with some tasks that archived all my tweets into\nevernote and my favorites. I’m sure I’ll go over it tonight to see what\nelse I can do with it that would be relevant to my interests.</p>\n<p>There’s also <a href=\"http://zapier.com/\">zapier.com</a> (Thanks Jordan S) which can also do the same\nthing, but with different “channels/apps” most noted, GitHub and JIRA!</p>\n<p>For mobile users, there’s <a href=\"https://www.onx.ms/\">on{x}</a>, where you can script events on your\nphone to do certain things. Best bit is that it’s written in JavaScript\n– so you can do quite a bit with it. I haven’t played around with it\nyet, but I’m sure I will in the near future.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Automate my everythings","date":"2012, Jun 13","tags":["home-automation","systems"],"img":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/3